Sec. 8-75. - Administrative fees for insurers insuring certain risks. 
Pursuant to O.C.G.A. § 33-8-8, for each separate business location, not otherwise subject to an administrative fee hereunder, operated and maintained by a business organization that is engaged in the business of lending money or transacting sales involving term financing and in connection with such loans or sales, offers, solicits or takes application for insurance through a licensed agent of an insurer for insurance said insurer shall pay an administrative license fee in the amount established by the City Council. The administrative fee assessed in this section is due January 1 of each year. 
(Code 1997, § 4-108(2); Ord. of 7-11-2011(01), § 1; Ord. of 12-05-2011(01), § 1) 
