(Ord. of 12-5-2011(05), § 11-109; Ord. of 8-6-2012(01), § 1(11-109); Ord. of 9-6-2016, § 1) 
Sec. 34-60. - Reduction of speed when speed hazards exist. 
Regardless of minimum and maximum speeds established in this division and by state law, no person in the City shall drive a vehicle on a street or highway at a speed greater than is reasonable and prudent under the existing conditions and with due regard for the actual and potential hazards that exist. In every event speed shall be so controlled as may be necessary to avoid colliding with any person, vehicle or other conveyance on or entering the street, road, highway or other avenues of travel, in compliance with legal requirements and the duty of all persons to use due care and caution. 
State Law reference— Alteration of speed limits by local authorities, O.C.G.A. § 40-6-183.

