b.  Patios permitted for outdoor dining. 
c.  Awning depth: four feet, maximum. 

(b)  Type 2, mixed-use building. 

(1)  Description. A mixed-use building has two or more floors, and allows the flexibility of having a vertical mixture of uses. The ground floor may be used for retail or office uses, while upper floors may be used for office, residential or lodging. 
(2)  Mixed-use standards. 
a.  Height regulations. 
